<h2 id="advanced-features">Advanced Features</h2>
<h3 id="blockquotes">Blockquotes</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>“The best way to learn markdown is by using it regularly.”</p>
</blockquote>
<h4 id="nested-blockquotes">Nested Blockquotes</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>This is a top-level quote.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This is a nested quote within the first quote.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And this is even more deeply nested.</p>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>
<h4 id="blockquotes-with-other-elements">Blockquotes with Other
Elements</h4>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This is an important point.</p>
<p>You can include other markdown elements inside blockquotes: - Lists -
<em>Formatting</em> - <code>Code</code></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="horizontal-rules">Horizontal Rules</h3>
<p>You can create horizontal rules using three or more dashes,
asterisks, or underscores:</p>
<hr />
<hr />
<hr />
<h3 id="escape-characters">Escape Characters</h3>
<p>Sometimes you need to display markdown characters literally. Use
backslashes to escape them:</p>
<p>*This text is not italic* # This is not a header `This is not
code`</p>
<h3 id="html-in-markdown">HTML in Markdown</h3>
<p>For advanced formatting, you can include HTML:</p>
<div style="text-align: center; color: blue;">
<p>This text is centered and blue using HTML.</p>
</div>
<details>
<summary>
Click to expand
</summary>
<p>This content is hidden by default and can be expanded by clicking the
summary.</p>
</details>
